{"type":"text","timestamp":1777761406805,"sessionID":"ses_2152b142effeJaBnw8lpnjlVpu","part":{"id":"prt_dead636fc001Zn4x8Qy6rfyxoH","messageID":"msg_dead63282001DE0m26t1m0JOxO","sessionID":"ses_2152b142effeJaBnw8lpnjlVpu","type":"text","text":"Wrote `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-001-r2s0.yaml`.\n\nHypothesis summary: **Share a single 33x33 signed multiplier across all four M-ext multiply variants** (MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU).\n\nReasoning:\n- `alu.sv` currently instantiates three parallel 64-bit multiplications (`mul_ss`, `mul_uu`, `mul_su`) and muxes one output. On Gowin GW2AR-18 this costs ~3× the DSP/LUT footprint vs. a single sign-aware 33×33.\n- All four RV32M multiply variants reduce to one signed 33×33 with per-op operand sign-extension: `MULH` sets both signs, `MULHSU` sets only `sign_a`, `MULHU`/`MUL` set neither; MUL reads the low 32 bits, the three `*H*` variants read `[63:32]`.\n- Targets the same Fmax-critical EX-stage combinational cone that the DIV-extraction win (+13.29%) shrank — so it lines up with the winning lesson from iteration 2.\n- Keeps the `RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS` branch byte-identical, preserving per-iteration formal BMC tractability.\n- IPC unchanged; MUL/MULH* stay single-cycle. Risk is confined to one file and covered by existing `test_alu.py` + cosim diff against the Python ISS.\n- Avoids the failure modes of the last three iterations: no PC-path rework (JAL-early regression), no new predictor state (BTB regression), pure area/Fmax play.\n\nExpected fitness delta: +4% (medium confidence).","time":{"start":1777761400572,"end":1777761406804}}}
