{"type":"text","timestamp":1777759417942,"sessionID":"ses_21549585fffePPezGHdBpHeucc","part":{"id":"prt_deab7e4bd001ArPAsIyxR4LgrJ","messageID":"msg_deab7daf4001cRMgpEZTKhMWIq","sessionID":"ses_21549585fffePPezGHdBpHeucc","type":"text","text":"Wrote the hypothesis to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-002-r1s1.yaml`.\n\n**Summary:** Structural proposal to extract RV32M DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU out of the combinational ALU into a new `div_unit.sv` — a 32-cycle iterative restoring divider with pipeline stall integration. Rationale: on Tang Nano 20K (no DSP division support), the combinational 32-bit divider is almost certainly both the Fmax-limiting critical path AND a major LUT4 consumer. MUL stays combinational (maps to Gowin DSPs cleanly). CoreMark does very little division, so the ~32-cycle latency per rare DIV is a tiny IPC tax compared to the expected 15–25% Fmax gain. ALTOPS formal path is untouched so per-iteration formal gate stays fast. Invariant 5b preserved via updated `test_alu.py` vectors and `make formal-deep` periodic check. Expected fitness delta: +12%.","time":{"start":1777759413437,"end":1777759417941}}}
