{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777761361188,"sessionID":"ses_2152b14fcffeYqX4a4nkZR1rkD","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"toolu_bdrk_01VP5LFmuWNNS88ZhdcRcNnE","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"structural|prefetch|fetch.*buffer|FIFO|skid","path":"cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl"},"output":"Found 2 matches\n/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl:\n  Line 3: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260502-002-r1s1\", \"title\": \"Extract DIV/REM into iterative multi-cycle unit to shorten ALU critical path\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"motivation\": \"The current ALU is fully combinational \\u2014 every op, including 32-bit signed/unsigned\\ndivision and remainder, is computed in a single EX-stage cycle via SystemVerilog\\n`/` and `%`. On the Tang Nano 20K (Gowin GW2AR-18) there are no DSP blocks that\\nmap division; synthesis emits a restoring-divider tree that is almost certainly\\nBOTH the timing-critical path AND a significant LUT4 consumer.\\n\\nCurrent fitness is Fmax-dominated: 135.21 MHz on a 5-stage in-order pipeline is\\nlow for a design this simple. Removing the combinational divider should let the\\nEX stage re-close timing around just the adder/shifter/logic/comparator and\\nDSP-backed multiplier, freeing considerable slack.\\n\\nCoreMark performs very few DIV/REM ops (the hot loops are integer add/shift/\\ncompare/MUL and memcpy-like stores). Paying 32 cycles for a rare DIV is a\\ngreat trade when every other instruction gets a shorter clock period.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current ALU is fully combinational \\u2014 every op, including 32-bit signed/unsigned\\ndivision and remainder, is computed in a single EX-stage cycle via SystemVerilog\\n`/` and `%`. On the Tang Nano 20K (Gowin GW2AR-18) there are no DSP blocks that\\nmap division; synthesis emits a restoring-divider tree that is almost certainly\\nBOTH the timing-critical path AND a significant LUT4 consumer.\\n\\nCurrent fitness is Fmax-dominated: 135.21 MHz on a 5-stage in-order pipeline is\\nlow for a design this simple. Removing the combinational divider should let the\\nEX stage re-close timing around just the adder/shifter/logic/comparator and\\nDSP-backed multiplier, freeing considerable slack.\\n\\nCoreMark performs very few DIV/REM ops (the hot loops are integer add/shift/\\ncompare/MUL and memcpy-like stores). Paying 32 cycles for a rare DIV is a\\ngreat trade when every other instruction g...\n  Line 4: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260502-003-r1s2\", \"title\": \"IF-stage BTB + bimodal predictor to eliminate taken-branch bubbles\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"Today the 5-stage in-order pipeline resolves every control transfer in\\nEX. A taken branch or jump flushes two in-flight instructions (the one\\nin IF->ID this cycle, plus the one captured into ID/EX next cycle), so\\nevery taken CTI costs a fixed 2-cycle bubble. Untaken conditional\\nbranches cost 0 because the static predict-not-taken path matches the\\npc+4 default fetch.\\n\\nCoreMark is branch-dense: the inner loops of matrix_mul_matrix_bitextract,\\ncore_list_mergesort, crc16, and core_bench_state all spin on backward\\nbranches that are taken the overwhelming majority of the time, plus\\nevery function call/return is a JAL + JALR pair that unconditionally\\ncosts the 2-cycle bubble today. Back-of-the-envelope: if taken CTIs\\nare ~15% of retired instructions (typical for integer workloads) and\\nwe pay 2 bubble cycles each, that is ~30% CPI overhead attributable\\nto branches alone. Even a modest-accuracy predictor that covers the\\nhot loops and function returns should claw back a large chunk of that.\\n\\nThere is headroom in the LUT budget (9880/10000) but it is tight, and\\nFmax is already at 135 MHz. The predictor must be cheap and must not\\nsit on the IF critical path.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"Today the 5-stage in-order pipeline resolves every control transfer in\\nEX. A taken branch or jump flushes two in-flight instructions (the one\\nin IF->ID this cycle, plus the one captured into ID/EX next cycle), so\\nevery taken CTI costs a fixed 2-cycle bubble. Untaken conditional\\nbranches cost 0 because the static predict-not-taken path matches the\\npc+4 default fetch.\\n\\nCoreMark is branch-dense: the inner loops of matrix_mul_matrix_bitextract,\\ncore_list_mergesort, crc16, and core_bench_state all spin on backward\\nbranches that are taken the overwhelming majority of the time, plus\\nevery function call/return is a JAL + ...","metadata":{"matches":2,"truncated":false},"title":"structural|prefetch|fetch.*buffer|FIFO|skid","time":{"start":1777761361181,"end":1777761361187}},"metadata":{"openrouter":{"reasoning_details":[]}},"id":"prt_dead59b43001NWco1Mkfy9rRyb","sessionID":"ses_2152b14fcffeYqX4a4nkZR1rkD","messageID":"msg_dead59638001ocg061LwyF9oO9"}}
