{"type":"text","timestamp":1777761408836,"sessionID":"ses_2152b14fcffeYqX4a4nkZR1rkD","part":{"id":"prt_dead64516002R1LLoLmnnjM7dm","messageID":"msg_dead63f04001c3vaOhFJQ6wCe7","sessionID":"ses_2152b14fcffeYqX4a4nkZR1rkD","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-002-r2s1.yaml`.\n\n**Summary:** Structural change — insert a 2-entry decoupled instruction-fetch FIFO between imem response and IF/ID, so iStall bubbles and ID-side backpressure no longer force retirement bubbles.\n\n**Rationale grounded in prior lessons:**\n- hyp-001 (JAL early-redirect) and hyp-003 (BTB) both regressed by widening/complicating the IF-PC mux. This proposal is deliberately *queue-side only* — PC→imem_addr stays identical, no new PC-mux tier, no branch comparator.\n- Fitness benchmark runs under ~22% iStall/dStall cosim methodology; every iStall cycle is currently a straight-through retirement bubble. A 2-entry FIFO plus decoupled pop/push should recover ~50–70% of those.\n- LUT budget is healthy (5433/10000 after DIV extraction) — ~120 LUT cost is affordable.\n- Zero RVFI/invariant surface changes: retirement stays at MEM/WB, channel-1 stays tied off, rvfi_order monotonicity untouched.\n\nExpected delta: +5%, confidence medium.","time":{"start":1777761404182,"end":1777761408835}}}
