{"type":"text","timestamp":1777762615332,"sessionID":"ses_215194dc6ffe7gz58Vlg837cxp","part":{"id":"prt_deae8ab770010oCf6w8ux707fb","messageID":"msg_deae8a453001ym52ZgYmGEUiG4","sessionID":"ses_215194dc6ffe7gz58Vlg837cxp","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-002-r3s1.yaml`.\n\n**Summary:** Pipelined 1-cycle MUL unit — extract MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU from the combinational ALU into a new `mul_unit.sv` with a registered result, mirroring the proven +13.29% DIV extraction pattern.\n\n**Key design choices to avoid prior pitfalls:**\n- Register placed *after* the DSP product (not before, unlike the -3.93% r2s0 failure which added a pre-multiplier sign mux).\n- Keeps the three parallel mul_ss/mul_uu/mul_su computations internal to mul_unit — lets synthesis DCE/share as it already does. No operand widening.\n- ALTOPS branch in alu.sv is identical (formal BMC stays tractable).\n- Hazard integration reuses the existing div_stall fan-out pattern verbatim.\n- PC/fetch path is untouched (per r1s0 lesson) and no new pipeline bundle widening (per r1s2 lesson).\n\nCost: ~1 cycle per MUL (a few thousand cycles against 4.5M total = <0.2% IPC loss). Expected gain: 8–15% Fmax from breaking the EX critical path, netting ~+8% fitness.","time":{"start":1777762610039,"end":1777762615331}}}
