{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777762687750,"sessionID":"ses_215180ec9ffe1VAkuriDx3NWc9","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_bdrk_01KuZFFD8H1U5FzfA48Np3JS","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Implementation notes — regfile reset removal + LUTRAM-shaped storage\n\n## What changed\n\nOnly `cores/bench/rtl/reg_file.sv` and `cores/bench/test/test_reg_file.py`.\n\n### `rtl/reg_file.sv`\n- Removed the synchronous-reset clear loop on the `regs[]` array. The\n  storage is now a single-write, no-reset `always_ff` block — the\n  shape Gowin Yosys + synth recognises for distributed LUTRAM (SPX9 /\n  SDPB) inference on a 32x32 2R1W memory.\n- Kept the x0 write-guard (`w_en && w_addr != 5'b0`) INSIDE the\n  always_ff, exactly as the hypothesis prescribes, so `regs[0]` is\n  never captured. Yosys accepts this conditional-write shape for\n  LUTRAM; it is not a reset net.\n- Kept the x0=0 short-circuit as the outermost read-port mux\n  (`rs_addr == 0 ? 0 : ...`) so reads of x0 are independent of\n  whatever `regs[0]` happens to hold.\n- Kept the write-first bypass as an explicit combinational mux between\n  the x0 mux and the RAM output (`(w_en && w_addr == rs_addr) ?\n  w_data : regs[rs_addr]`). Gowin distributed RAM doesn't emit\n  write-first on 2R1W same-cycle reads, so the bypass stays external\n  — a couple of LUT4s per read port.\n- `reset` port retained (top-level wiring in `core.sv` drives it) but\n  unused in the body; silenced with a local `verilator lint_off\n  UNUSEDSIGNAL` pragma.\n\n### `test/test_reg_file.py`\n- Replaced the old `reset_clears_all` (which read every register after\n  reset and expected 0) with `reset_x0_reads_zero` — we only assert\n  the x0 invariant post-reset, because non-x0 storage is legitimately\n  indeterminate in the LUTRAM configuration.\n- Kept `write_and_read`, `x0_hardwired`, `write_first_bypass`, and\n  `two_read_ports` from the original suite (unchanged semantics).\n- Extended `x0_hardwired` with a same-cycle write-to-x0 + read-x0\n  check to lock in the \"read mux wins over any storage contents\"\n  property even while the write is in flight.\n- Added `full_sweep_write_then_read`: writes a distinct `0xDEAD00 |\n  r` to every non-x0 register (r in [1..31]) and reads them all back.\n  This is the hypothesis-specified \"write/read round-trip for every\n  non-x0 register\" test plus doubles as a 32-deep sweep.\n\n## Deviations from the plan\n\nNone substantive. The hypothesis file was followed exactly — reset\nremoved, x0 mux kept external, write-first bypass kept external,\nwrite-guard kept inside the always_ff.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `verilator --lint-only -Wall -Wno-MULTITOP -sv` on all of\n  `cores/bench/rtl/*.sv`: clean, no warnings.\n- `bash formal/run_all.sh`: **105 passed, 0 failed**. Full\n  riscv-formal NRET=2 check set including `reg_ch0` (the register-\n  file consistency check) passes.\n\n## Concerns / risk\n\n- If Gowin synth for whatever reason declines to infer distributed RAM\n  from this shape (unusual opcode combining, undocumented limit on\n  conditional-write patterns, etc.), the fallback is the default\n  all-flops inference — functionally identical, just no LUT/FF saving.\n  That's the downside case; upside is the hypothesis-projected few\n  hundred LUTs + ~1000 FFs freed.\n- Architectural correctness under power-on / indeterminate storage:\n  RV32I programs (including crt0 and CoreMark) are responsible for\n  writing every live register before reading it; the x0 read-mux\n  guarantees the one register whose post-reset value is architecturally\n  visible. riscv-formal's `reg_ch0` check passes, which confirms that\n  the regfile semantics (including the write-first bypass and x0\n  hardwiring) are preserved bit-for-bit for every retired instruction\n  the solver can synthesize.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep1/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260502-001-r3s0/cores/bench/implementation_notes.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep1/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260502-001-r3s0/cores/bench/implementation_notes.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/implementation_notes.md","time":{"start":1777762687747,"end":1777762687749}},"metadata":{"openrouter":{"reasoning_details":[]}},"id":"prt_deae98bfb0015ruJSfTkJAE5Hn","sessionID":"ses_215180ec9ffe1VAkuriDx3NWc9","messageID":"msg_deae98560001PsiriG7iTk7Vis"}}
