{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777762678314,"sessionID":"ses_215173982ffecHKL5CIJz8yL90","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"todowrite","callID":"toolu_bdrk_01JvEZuNcbZpgRdUVHqq5j18","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"todos":[{"content":"Create rtl/mul_unit.sv","status":"in_progress","priority":"high"},{"content":"Modify rtl/alu.sv to remove MUL from non-ALTOPS path","status":"pending","priority":"high"},{"content":"Modify rtl/ex_stage.sv to dispatch MUL to mul_unit","status":"pending","priority":"high"},{"content":"Modify rtl/hazard_unit.sv to add mul_stall input","status":"pending","priority":"high"},{"content":"Modify rtl/core.sv to wire mul_stall","status":"pending","priority":"high"},{"content":"Update tests: migrate MUL vectors to test_mul_unit.py, update test_alu.py and test_pipeline.py","status":"pending","priority":"high"},{"content":"Verilator lint and local formal","status":"pending","priority":"high"}]},"output":"[\n  {\n    \"content\": \"Create rtl/mul_unit.sv\",\n    \"status\": \"in_progress\",\n    \"priority\": \"high\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"content\": \"Modify rtl/alu.sv to remove MUL from non-ALTOPS path\",\n    \"status\": \"pending\",\n    \"priority\": \"high\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"content\": \"Modify rtl/ex_stage.sv to dispatch MUL to mul_unit\",\n    \"status\": \"pending\",\n    \"priority\": \"high\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"content\": \"Modify rtl/hazard_unit.sv to add mul_stall input\",\n    \"status\": \"pending\",\n    \"priority\": \"high\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"content\": \"Modify rtl/core.sv to wire mul_stall\",\n    \"status\": \"pending\",\n    \"priority\": \"high\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"content\": \"Update tests: migrate MUL vectors to test_mul_unit.py, update test_alu.py and test_pipeline.py\",\n    \"status\": \"pending\",\n    \"priority\": \"high\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"content\": \"Verilator lint and local formal\",\n    \"status\": \"pending\",\n    \"priority\": \"high\"\n  }\n]","metadata":{"todos":[{"content":"Create rtl/mul_unit.sv","status":"in_progress","priority":"high"},{"content":"Modify rtl/alu.sv to remove MUL from non-ALTOPS path","status":"pending","priority":"high"},{"content":"Modify rtl/ex_stage.sv to dispatch MUL to mul_unit","status":"pending","priority":"high"},{"content":"Modify rtl/hazard_unit.sv to add mul_stall input","status":"pending","priority":"high"},{"content":"Modify rtl/core.sv to wire mul_stall","status":"pending","priority":"high"},{"content":"Update tests: migrate MUL vectors to test_mul_unit.py, update test_alu.py and test_pipeline.py","status":"pending","priority":"high"},{"content":"Verilator lint and local formal","status":"pending","priority":"high"}],"truncated":false},"title":"7 todos","time":{"start":1777762678312,"end":1777762678313}},"metadata":{"openrouter":{"reasoning_details":[{"type":"reasoning.text","text":" I'm mapping out the implementation strategy: I need to create a new pipelined multiplier unit with a simple two-state FSM, strip multiplication operations from the main ALU to return zero like division does, and then wire everything together in the execution stage.\n\nNow I'm clarifying the timing—the multiplier takes one cycle to compute and register the result, then pulses done on the next cycle, giving a net latency of one cycle which matches the DIV unit's behavior. Looking at the dispatch logic in ex_stage, when a multiply operation enters the execute stage at cycle T, the start signal fires and stalls the pipeline. Then at T+1, the done signal asserts and the stall clears, allowing the result to be captured into EX/MEM—adding one cycle of latency. I should implement the multiply unit following the same pattern as the divider, with the state machine transitioning through IDLE → COMPLETE and back.\n\nDefining the mul_unit module... I'm seeing the state machine logic now — when we're in S_COMPLETE, busy is still asserted because state_q isn't S_IDLE, which makes sense since the unit isn't ready for a new operation yet. The done signal gives us that one-cycle pulse. I need to mirror the div_unit's dispatch pattern in ex_stage, update the ALU to zero out the multiply operations in the non-ALTOPS path, and add the mul_stall input to the hazard unit so it can OR it with the other stall conditions.\n\nLet me be careful with the ifdef structure in alu.sv — the ALTOPS branch needs to stay unchanged with its XOR patterns, but the else branch should return zero for MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU and also drop the internal mul_ss/mul_uu/mul_su signals entirely.\n\nNow I need to handle the test suite: the MUL tests in test_alu.py probe the ALU directly, but since we're moving MUL handling to mul_unit, I should migrate those tests to a new test_mul_unit.py that uses the handshake protocol instead.\n\nI also want to add a mul_stall test to test_pipeline.py similar to the existing div_stalls_pipeline_then_retires test.\n\nFor the hazard_unit changes, I'm adding mul_stall to the stall conditions: it needs to gate stall_id, stall_ex_mem, hold_mem_wb, and the flush logic, while ibuf_pop automatically stays correct since it already depends on stall_id.\n\nUpdating hazard_unit logic...","format":"anthropic-claude-v1","index":0,"signature":""}]}},"id":"prt_deae9b3c1001wL34EjaQGg6j8m","sessionID":"ses_215173982ffecHKL5CIJz8yL90","messageID":"msg_deae9102a001jhRpWpzjlihdSv"}}
