{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777762732974,"sessionID":"ses_215173982ffecHKL5CIJz8yL90","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_bdrk_0177JA87bUeHgZHzYJHEhb4F","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"// rtl/alu.sv\n//\n// RV32I combinational ALU — base RV32I only. The M-extension operators\n// live outside the combinational EX cone:\n//\n//   * DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU -> iterative `div_unit` (33 cycles real divide,\n//                           2 cycles fast path).\n//   * MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU -> pipelined 1-cycle `mul_unit`. Removing\n//                           the three 32x32->64 partial-product trees\n//                           and their 64-wide output mux from this\n//                           module is what frees Fmax to close around\n//                           just add/shift/logic/compare.\n//\n// In the real-arithmetic build (cocotb / cosim / FPGA), MUL/MULH/MULHU/\n// MULHSU and DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU default to '0 here and the iterative\n// units drive the final EX-stage result via ex_stage's alu_result_final\n// mux.\n//\n// Under `RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS` the M-extension operators are replaced\n// with the riscv-formal XOR-of-add/sub stand-ins so bitwuzla solves the\n// BMC inside the 20-step budget. In that mode all eight M-ext operators\n// resolve combinationally here — neither the div_unit nor the mul_unit\n// is instantiated in ex_stage, and the ALU stays the sole source of\n// the EX-stage result.\n//\n// Latency:        combinational (0 cycles).\n// RVFI fields:    feeds rd_wdata (via EX/MEM/WB), branch resolution, mem_addr.\nmodule alu (\n  input  logic [4:0]  op,\n  input  logic [31:0] a,\n  input  logic [31:0] b,\n  output logic [31:0] out\n);\n\n  logic [4:0] shamt;\n\n  always_comb begin\n    shamt = b[4:0];\n\n    case (op)\n      ALU_ADD:    out = a + b;\n      ALU_SUB:    out = a - b;\n      ALU_AND:    out = a & b;\n      ALU_OR:     out = a | b;\n      ALU_XOR:    out = a ^ b;\n      ALU_SLT:    out = {31'b0, $signed(a) < $signed(b)};\n      ALU_SLTU:   out = {31'b0, a < b};\n      ALU_SLL:    out = a << shamt;\n      ALU_SRL:    out = a >> shamt;\n      ALU_SRA:    out = $unsigned($signed(a) >>> shamt);\n      ALU_LUI:    out = b;\n\n      // M-extension. Under RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS the hardware operations\n      // are substituted for tractable algebraic stand-ins so bitwuzla\n      // can solve the BMC inside the 20-step depth budget. The same\n      // substitution must appear in the riscv-formal spec (insn_*.v).\n      // The Verilator/cocotb/cosim builds leave ALTOPS undefined and\n      // run the real arithmetic through the iterative units in ex_stage.\n`ifdef RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS\n      ALU_MUL:    out = (a + b) ^ 32'h5876063e;\n      ALU_MULH:   out = (a + b) ^ 32'hf6583fb7;\n      ALU_MULHU:  out = (a + b) ^ 32'h949ce5e8;\n      ALU_MULHSU: out = (a - b) ^ 32'hecfbe137;\n      ALU_DIV:    out = (a - b) ^ 32'h7f8529ec;\n      ALU_DIVU:   out = (a - b) ^ 32'h10e8fd70;\n      ALU_REM:    out = (a - b) ^ 32'h8da68fa5;\n      ALU_REMU:   out = (a - b) ^ 32'h3138d0e1;\n`else\n      // MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU: handled by mul_unit in ex_stage.\n      // DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU:     handled by div_unit in ex_stage.\n      // The ALU deliberately returns '0 here so any attempt to read a\n      // M-ext op's result straight out of the ALU (pre-mux) is\n      // obviously bogus rather than silently passing an unrelated\n      // combinational value through EX/MEM. ex_stage's alu_result_final\n      // mux replaces this with the iterative unit's result on the\n      // completion cycle.\n      ALU_MUL,\n      ALU_MULH,\n      ALU_MULHU,\n      ALU_MULHSU,\n      ALU_DIV,\n      ALU_DIVU,\n      ALU_REM,\n      ALU_REMU:   out = 32'b0;\n`endif\n      default:    out = 32'b0;\n    endcase\n  end\n\nendmodule\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep1/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260502-002-r3s1/cores/bench/rtl/alu.sv"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep1/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260502-002-r3s1/cores/bench/rtl/alu.sv","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/rtl/alu.sv","time":{"start":1777762732958,"end":1777762732973}},"metadata":{"openrouter":{"reasoning_details":[]}},"id":"prt_deaea4c93001SctDOmCG5Sv76s","sessionID":"ses_215173982ffecHKL5CIJz8yL90","messageID":"msg_deaea3c210010Wj52W4VzAuCBl"}}
