{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777762773024,"sessionID":"ses_215173982ffecHKL5CIJz8yL90","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"toolu_bdrk_014E6q5biecxQQvJ2nzEqLAH","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep1/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260502-002-r3s1/cores/bench/rtl/ex_stage.sv","newString":"// Under `RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS` (the fast per-iteration formal mode):\n//   DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU and MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU resolve combinationally\n//   through the ALU's XOR stand-ins — identical to the V0 baseline —\n//   and no iterative units are instantiated. div_stall_o and\n//   mul_stall_o are tied to 0. This keeps bitwuzla BMC tractable.\n//\n// Under the real-arithmetic build (cocotb, cosim, FPGA):\n//   DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU dispatch to an iterative 32-cycle `div_unit`.\n//   MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU dispatch to a pipelined 1-cycle `mul_unit`\n//   (register sits after the DSP product to break the EX critical\n//   path). Both units run in parallel with the combinational ALU; on\n//   completion, alu_result_final muxes the iterative unit's result\n//   over the ALU's '0 placeholder. While either unit is computing,\n//   the corresponding *_stall_o is asserted and the hazard_unit\n//   freezes ID/EX, EX/MEM, and MEM/WB. Redirect from a branch cannot\n//   coexist with a DIV or MUL in EX (mutually exclusive by opcode),\n//   so the existing redirect/flush logic is untouched.","oldString":"// Under `RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS` (the fast per-iteration formal mode):\n//   DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU resolve combinationally through the ALU's XOR\n//   stand-ins — identical to the V0 baseline — and no div_unit is\n//   instantiated. The div_stall output is tied to 0. This keeps\n//   bitwuzla BMC tractable.\n//\n// Under the real-arithmetic build (cocotb, cosim, FPGA):\n//   DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU dispatch to an iterative 32-cycle `div_unit`.\n//   The unit runs in parallel with the combinational ALU; on\n//   completion, alu_result_final muxes du_result over the ALU's '0\n//   placeholder. While the unit is computing, div_stall_o is asserted\n//   and the hazard_unit freezes ID/EX, EX/MEM, and MEM/WB. Redirect\n//   from a branch cannot coexist with a DIV in EX (mutually exclusive\n//   by opcode), so the existing redirect/flush logic is untouched."},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep1/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260502-002-r3s1/cores/bench/rtl/ex_stage.sv\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep1/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260502-002-r3s1/cores/bench/rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep1/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260502-002-r3s1/cores/bench/rtl/ex_stage.sv\n@@ -4,21 +4,24 @@\n // MEM/WB), runs the ALU, resolves branches, computes the redirect\n // target. Owns the EX/MEM pipeline register.\n //\n // Under `RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS` (the fast per-iteration formal mode):\n-//   DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU resolve combinationally through the ALU's XOR\n-//   stand-ins — identical to the V0 baseline — and no div_unit is\n-//   instantiated. The div_stall output is tied to 0. This keeps\n-//   bitwuzla BMC tractable.\n+//   DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU and MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU resolve combinationally\n+//   through the ALU's XOR stand-ins — identical to the V0 baseline —\n+//   and no iterative units are instantiated. div_stall_o and\n+//   mul_stall_o are tied to 0. This keeps bitwuzla BMC tractable.\n //\n // Under the real-arithmetic build (cocotb, cosim, FPGA):\n //   DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU dispatch to an iterative 32-cycle `div_unit`.\n-//   The unit runs in parallel with the combinational ALU; on\n-//   completion, alu_result_final muxes du_result over the ALU's '0\n-//   placeholder. While the unit is computing, div_stall_o is asserted\n-//   and the hazard_unit freezes ID/EX, EX/MEM, and MEM/WB. Redirect\n-//   from a branch cannot coexist with a DIV in EX (mutually exclusive\n-//   by opcode), so the existing redirect/flush logic is untouched.\n+//   MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU dispatch to a pipelined 1-cycle `mul_unit`\n+//   (register sits after the DSP product to break the EX critical\n+//   path). Both units run in parallel with the combinational ALU; on\n+//   completion, alu_result_final muxes the iterative unit's result\n+//   over the ALU's '0 placeholder. While either unit is computing,\n+//   the corresponding *_stall_o is asserted and the hazard_unit\n+//   freezes ID/EX, EX/MEM, and MEM/WB. Redirect from a branch cannot\n+//   coexist with a DIV or MUL in EX (mutually exclusive by opcode),\n+//   so the existing redirect/flush logic is untouched.\n //\n // Forwarding select encoding (driven by forward_unit):\n //   00 = ID/EX register value (no forward)\n //   01 = EX/MEM aluResult (instruction immediately ahead in MEM)\n","filediff":{"file":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep1/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260502-002-r3s1/cores/bench/rtl/ex_stage.sv","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep1/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260502-002-r3s1/cores/bench/rtl/ex_stage.sv\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep1/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260502-002-r3s1/cores/bench/rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep1/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260502-002-r3s1/cores/bench/rtl/ex_stage.sv\n@@ -4,21 +4,24 @@\n // MEM/WB), runs the ALU, resolves branches, computes the redirect\n // target. Owns the EX/MEM pipeline register.\n //\n // Under `RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS` (the fast per-iteration formal mode):\n-//   DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU resolve combinationally through the ALU's XOR\n-//   stand-ins — identical to the V0 baseline — and no div_unit is\n-//   instantiated. The div_stall output is tied to 0. This keeps\n-//   bitwuzla BMC tractable.\n+//   DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU and MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU resolve combinationally\n+//   through the ALU's XOR stand-ins — identical to the V0 baseline —\n+//   and no iterative units are instantiated. div_stall_o and\n+//   mul_stall_o are tied to 0. This keeps bitwuzla BMC tractable.\n //\n // Under the real-arithmetic build (cocotb, cosim, FPGA):\n //   DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU dispatch to an iterative 32-cycle `div_unit`.\n-//   The unit runs in parallel with the combinational ALU; on\n-//   completion, alu_result_final muxes du_result over the ALU's '0\n-//   placeholder. While the unit is computing, div_stall_o is asserted\n-//   and the hazard_unit freezes ID/EX, EX/MEM, and MEM/WB. Redirect\n-//   from a branch cannot coexist with a DIV in EX (mutually exclusive\n-//   by opcode), so the existing redirect/flush logic is untouched.\n+//   MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU dispatch to a pipelined 1-cycle `mul_unit`\n+//   (register sits after the DSP product to break the EX critical\n+//   path). Both units run in parallel with the combinational ALU; on\n+//   completion, alu_result_final muxes the iterative unit's result\n+//   over the ALU's '0 placeholder. While either unit is computing,\n+//   the corresponding *_stall_o is asserted and the hazard_unit\n+//   freezes ID/EX, EX/MEM, and MEM/WB. Redirect from a branch cannot\n+//   coexist with a DIV or MUL in EX (mutually exclusive by opcode),\n+//   so the existing redirect/flush logic is untouched.\n //\n // Forwarding select encoding (driven by forward_unit):\n //   00 = ID/EX register value (no forward)\n //   01 = EX/MEM aluResult (instruction immediately ahead in MEM)\n","additions":13,"deletions":10},"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/rtl/ex_stage.sv","time":{"start":1777762773021,"end":1777762773022}},"metadata":{"openrouter":{"reasoning_details":[]}},"id":"prt_deaeb03f1001y3nyz1AyyLtsnc","sessionID":"ses_215173982ffecHKL5CIJz8yL90","messageID":"msg_deaeafa4b0016DLt2WnFi2048x"}}
